		&lt;command&gt;show&lt;/command&gt;
	    &lt;category&gt;host&lt;/category&gt;
		&lt;process-id&gt;find-host-details&lt;/process-id&gt;
	    &lt;command-arguments&gt;
		  &lt;all/&gt;
	    &lt;/command-arguments&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
&lt;/items&gt;

Parameters Description:

command[Required]
	The actual command type that will be executed.
category[Required]
	This parameter identifies the top-level functional category.
process-id[Required]
	Unique identifier for the process workflow.
all[Required]
	Indicates that details of all the components on the hosts detected by the management server are required.

2. Provides a detailed description of the volume manager volumes on the host specified.

Sample Request XML:
&lt;items&gt;
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;command&gt;show&lt;/command&gt;
	    &lt;category&gt;host&lt;/category&gt;
		&lt;process-id&gt;find-host-details&lt;/process-id&gt;
	    &lt;command-arguments&gt;
		  &lt;volume/&gt;
		  &lt;host-id&gt;1759&lt;/host-id&gt;
	    &lt;/command-arguments&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
&lt;/items&gt;

Parameters Description:

command[Required]
	The actual command type that will be executed.
category[Required]
	This parameter identifies the top-level functional category.
process-id[Required]
	Unique identifier for the process workflow.
host-id[Required]
	id of the host whose details are required.
volume[Required]
	Indicates that details of volumes on the specified host are required.</description>
        <from>items</from>
        <to>items</to>
